06/11/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Police arrested two traffickers Wednesday (November 5th) outside the southern town of Saranda. They were allegedly transporting 11 illegal immigrants to neighbouring Greece. Police say the pair charged the immigrants 800 euros each.
In other news Wednesday, police in Gjirokastra seized 40kg of marijuana from a vehicle and arrested its driver. Authorities say the vehicle bore phony police licence plates and the driver wore a police vest. (BalkanWeb, Start, Vizion +, News 24 - 05/11/08)
